● ls
● mkdir
● cd


ls :- use to list out all the files and folders.
a. ls filename :- use to check whether the file exist ot not.
b. ls -l filename.sh :- use to check details of the file. 
c. ls -d directoryname :- use to check whether a dictionary exist or not.
d. ls dictionaryname :- use to check details of the dictionary. 
e. ls -a :- use to list out all the files and folders including hidden files.
f. ls *.txt :- use ti find file of a given type.

mkdir (make dictionary):- use to create dictionary with another dictionary OR use to create parent dictionary with child dictionary
a. mkdir ab :- use to make dictionary 
b. mkdir ab1 ab2 ab3 :-. use to create multiple dictionary 
c. mkdir ab4\xyz:- to create dictionary of any name with space. 
d. mkdir -p os1/theroy/D.

cd (change dictionary):-
a. cd ab xyz :- use to change dictionary 
b. cd.. :- use to gi back one step. 
c. cd ab/ xyz :- 
d. cd~ :- use to go back to route.
 
